    },
    {
      "id": "38a0ec8062e4f727fc8b57e704d226f79c88b59f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-05-22 04:51:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (2 inline comments)\n\nI'm fine with the general approach, and I have always disliked that there is complexity in the underlying filesystem that it doesn't know the block device and fstype used during mount.\n\nFor the proper patch, it of course needs a real LU ticket number, and in the future, please use LU-000 for fake ticket numbers, since LU-9999 will eventually conflict with some real ticket.\n\nPlease also use tabs for indentation on master, and we should begin using them on orion as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
